"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931008","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-03","<p>As at 31 March 2018 (the latest published data), 37 Foreign National Offenders were held at HM Prison Leicester and 107 were held at HM Prison Gartree.</p><p> </p><p>We are absolutely committed to removing Foreign National Offenders from the UK and continue to work closely with international governments to increase the number of prisoners deported. Since 2010, over 42,000 Foreign National Offenders have been removed from the United Kingdom.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-07-03T15:24:16.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931008/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931008/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931008/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-06-25","Prisoners: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many foreign national offenders are being held in prisons in Leicestershire.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","157040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931009","Department for International Development","false","2018-07-02","<p>The UK is at the forefront of international efforts to help stabilise Libya and to tackle the threat from Daesh and the migration crisis. Figures for total UK bilateral Overseas Development Assistance to Libya are published annually in the Statistics on International Development. In 2014 total bilateral ODA was £28.6m, in 2015 £10.4m, in 2016 £14.4m. Final figures for 2017 will be published later this year.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-02T16:48:18.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931009/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931009/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-06-25","Libya: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what estimate she has made of the cost to the public purse of development assistance to Libya in (a) 2014, (b) 2015, (c) 2016 and (d) 2017.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","157041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931010","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-02","<p>We continue to support the UN Special Envoy for Yemen in faciliating a credible peace process in Yemen. We have regular discussions with the Special Envoy and his office. The Foreign Secretary last spoke with the Special Envoy on 25 June. ​</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-02T16:29:11.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931010/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931010/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931010/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-25","Yemen: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the UN Special Envoy for Yemen on the peace process in that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","157042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931011","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-28","<p>Legislation does not specify a time limit within which an appeal against the establishment of a Business Improvement District must be decided. The Secretary of State will issue a decision as soon as possible, having taken account of all representations received from those with an interest in the appeal.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-06-28T16:23:04.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931011/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931011/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-25","Business Improvement Districts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether there is a timescale for the publication of the outcome of an appeal in a Business Improvement Districts bid.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","157229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931012","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-03","<p>The Government’s policy is that incineration should not compete with greater waste prevention, re-use and recycling. As part of the Government’s overall waste policy energy from waste plays a role in meeting the UK’s landfill diversion targets.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to recovering the maximum amount of energy from incinerated waste. It also encourages and supports the utilisation of heat and/or the production of other outputs beyond electricity.</p><p> </p><p>The Resource and Waste Strategy will be published later this year and will set out how we will maximise the value we get from resources and minimise waste. It will set out how we will achieve zero avoidable plastic waste, double the UK’s resource productivity by 2042, and achieve zero avoidable waste of all kinds by 2050.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-03T12:20:09.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931012/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931012/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-06-25","Incinerators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the Government’s policy is on the incineration of waste.","false","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","157122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931013","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-28","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not publish the names or specific details of Operational Pinch Points (OPPs) as this information would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces. However, I can assure the hon. Member that the Army has enough people to perform its operational requirements that help keep Britain safe.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum enlistment age for Soldiers into all Army Capbadges is 16, and it may be of interest to the hon. Member that of the current seven Army (OPPs) only one can be enlisted into. Pinch points may be rank or qualification specific and information is not held in the format requested to allow a more detailed response.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum enlistment age for soldiers into the Army is 16. We do not hold information about enlistment into OPPs in the specific format requested. However, of the current seven Army OPPs only one can be directly enlisted into because pinch points can be rank or qualification specific and therefore it is not always possible to enlist directly into them.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","157211 ; 157212","2018-06-28T14:51:24.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931013/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931013/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-25","Army: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which Army trades do not have an adequate number of trained regulars to perform operational tasks without taking mitigating actions; what the shortfall is in each such trade as a proportion of the number required; and what the minimum enlistment age is for each such trade.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","157210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931014","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-28","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not publish the names or specific details of Operational Pinch Points (OPPs) as this information would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces. However, I can assure the hon. Member that the Army has enough people to perform its operational requirements that help keep Britain safe.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum enlistment age for Soldiers into all Army Capbadges is 16, and it may be of interest to the hon. Member that of the current seven Army (OPPs) only one can be enlisted into. Pinch points may be rank or qualification specific and information is not held in the format requested to allow a more detailed response.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum enlistment age for soldiers into the Army is 16. We do not hold information about enlistment into OPPs in the specific format requested. However, of the current seven Army OPPs only one can be directly enlisted into because pinch points can be rank or qualification specific and therefore it is not always possible to enlist directly into them.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","157210 ; 157212","2018-06-28T14:51:25.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931014/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931014/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-25","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many and what proportion of soldiers who enlisted under the age of 18 were enlisted into pinch-point trades in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","157211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931015","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-28","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not publish the names or specific details of Operational Pinch Points (OPPs) as this information would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces. However, I can assure the hon. Member that the Army has enough people to perform its operational requirements that help keep Britain safe.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum enlistment age for Soldiers into all Army Capbadges is 16, and it may be of interest to the hon. Member that of the current seven Army (OPPs) only one can be enlisted into. Pinch points may be rank or qualification specific and information is not held in the format requested to allow a more detailed response.</p><p> </p><p>The minimum enlistment age for soldiers into the Army is 16. We do not hold information about enlistment into OPPs in the specific format requested. However, of the current seven Army OPPs only one can be directly enlisted into because pinch points can be rank or qualification specific and therefore it is not always possible to enlist directly into them.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","157210 ; 157211","2018-06-28T14:51:25.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931015/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931015/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-06-25","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average age of enlistment was for each soldier serving in a pinch-point trade.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","157212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/931016","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-03","<p>NHS Improvement publishes reference cost data relating to kidney transplants, which can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://improvement.nhs.uk/resources/reference-costs/" target="_blank">https://improvement.nhs.uk/resources/reference-costs/</a></p><p> </p><p>Reference costs are the average unit cost to the National Health Service of providing defined services to NHS patients in England in a given financial year. The information relating to kidney transplants is collected in two ways, the actual transplant episodes and the preparatory and follow-up screening and examinations in the case of live donor transplants. Reference costs for 2016-17 are given in the following tables.</p><p> </p><p>Reference costs for kidney transplant episodes 2016-17</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HRG<sup>1</sup> Description</p></td><td><p>Activity</p></td><td><p>Unit Cost</p></td><td><p>Total Cost</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kidney Transplant, 19 years and over, from Cadaver Non-Heart-Beating Donor</p></td><td><p>645</p></td><td><p>£12,167</p></td><td><p>£7,847,829</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kidney Transplant, 18 years and under, from Cadaver Non-Heart-Beating Donor</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>£5,780</p></td><td><p>£63,576</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kidney Transplant, 19 years and over, from Cadaver Heart-Beating Donor</p></td><td><p>1,171</p></td><td><p>£12,888</p></td><td><p>£15,092,002</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kidney Transplant, 18 years and under, from Cadaver Heart-Beating Donor</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>£15,157</p></td><td><p>£606,268</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kidney Transplant, 19 years and over, from Live Donor</p></td><td><p>708</p></td><td><p>£13,854</p></td><td><p>£9,808,873</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kidney Transplant, 18 years and under, from Live Donor</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>£15,149