"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928778","Home Office","false","2018-06-27","<p>The Government is considering a range of options for the future immigration system which will begin from 2021, and will set out initial plans later this year. We have asked the independent Migration Advisory committee (MAC) to advise on the economic and social impacts of the UK’s exit from the EU</p><p>The Government will have sufficient time to take account of the MAC’s advice when making any final decisions about our future immigration system, which would be implemented from 2021.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-27T13:31:44.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928778/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928778/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928778/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-06-21","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether he plans to publish a White Paper on immigration before the summer recess; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","156496"
