"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928791","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-28","<p>As set out in the answer I gave to the hon. Member on 20 June 2018 to Question 152643, this proposal was initiated following a proposal to InnovateUK, BEIS and the Department for Communities and Local Government, who agreed to this. No commissioning instructions were developed, as this work was supported as a matter of urgency.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-28T14:53:13.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928791/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928791/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-21","Fire Prevention: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 20 June 2018 to Question 152643, on fire prevention: insulation, if he will place in the Library the instructions used to commission the Manufacturing Technology Centre to look at the removal and replacement processes for cladding systems.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","156340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928792","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-28","<p>Funding for this project was provided by InnovateUK, an Executive Non-Departmental Public Body of the Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-06-28T14:53:48.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928792/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928792/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928792/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-21","Fire Prevention: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 20 June 2018 to Question 152643, on fire prevention: insulation, which Department funds the exploratory research and development.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","156341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928793","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-28","<p>The exploratory research and development project has been completed. The findings are currently being reviewed, and will be made available in due course.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","156338","2018-06-28T14:54:42.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928793/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928793/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928793/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-06-21","Fire Prevention: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 20 June 2018 to Question 152643, on Fire Prevention: Insulation, what the timetable is for the exploratory research and development to be completed.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","156342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928794","Department for Education","false","2018-06-28","<p>The Careers &amp; Enterprise Company has made excellent progress to date. It is building an Enterprise Adviser Network of business volunteers to work with schools and distributing funding so that more careers and enterprise activities reach young people in most need of support.</p><p> </p><p>The company will have an important role delivering the government’s careers strategy, including:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Working across all the Gatsby Benchmarks of good practice, instead of just those relating to employer engagement to test 20 Careers Hubs across England, backed by £5 million of government funding.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Expanding its Enterprise Adviser Network so that all secondary schools and colleges have access to an Enterprise Adviser by the end of 2020. The network will help schools and colleges give every young person at least seven encounters with employers during their secondary education.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Delivering a new £5 million Investment Fund to scale up careers and enterprise programmes for disadvantaged young people.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Training for 500 careers leaders in secondary schools and colleges, backed by £4 million of government funding.</li></ul><p> </p><p><br>More information about The Careers &amp; Enterprise Company’s activities can be found on their website: <a href="https://www.careersandenterprise.co.uk/" target="_blank">https://www.careersandenterprise.co.uk/</a>.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-06-28T10:59:33.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928794/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928794/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928794/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-06-21","Careers and Enterprise Company","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans he has for the future of the Careers and Enterprise Company; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","Hemel Hempstead","Sir Mike Penning","156377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928795","Treasury","false","2018-06-28","<p><em>To support British households and businesses, at Autumn Budget 2017, the government froze fuel duty for the eighth successive year. Since public finances are based on the assumption that fuel duty will increase with RPI at every Budget, any increase below this represents a cost to the Exchequer. Successive freezes since 2011 have saved the average driver £620 compared to what it would have been with RPI increases. </em></p><p><em>Since 2011, the announced freezes to fuel duty have meant the Exchequer has not collected around £46 billion in revenues through to 2018-19. For the purposes of comparison, this is around twice as much as we spend on all NHS nurses and doctors each year.</em></p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-28T09:48:31.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928795/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928795/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928795/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-06-21","Motor Vehicles: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the cost of (a) fuel duty and (b) road tax on the affordability of motoring.","false","Biography information for Ben Bradley","Mansfield","Ben Bradley","156489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928796","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-29","<p>As a strong supporter of a comprehensive and just Cyprus settlement based on the internationally accepted model of a bi-zonal, bi-communal federation, we regularly engage with the parties to the settlement talks at all levels<strong>. </strong>The Prime Minister discussed the issue with President Anastasiades in London on 17 April. I discussed the issue with Cypriot Foreign Minister Christodoulides on 20 April. The British Ambassador to Turkey discussed the issue with senior Turkish officials in mid-June. The Foreign Secretary last met with the parties at the Conference on Cyprus in Crans Montana, Switzerland on 27 June 2017.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-06-29T11:51:22.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928796/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928796/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928796/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-06-21","Cyprus: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his international counterparts on the re-unification of Cyprus.","false","Biography information for Ben Bradley","Mansfield","Ben Bradley","156490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928797","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-29","<p>Official level discussions in relation to this project started last year and are on going.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-06-29T15:40:34.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928797/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/928797/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-06-21","Fire Prevention: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what discussions Officials in his Department have had with Officials in the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the commissioning of the Manufacturing Technology Centre to review the removal and replacement processes for cladding systems.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","156343"
